        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 2:14AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 214 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Forreston to near Oregon to 7 miles
southeast of Rochelle. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oregon, Baileyville, Lindenwood, Ashton, Kings, Chana, Malta,
Cortland, Hillcrest, Steward, Stillman Valley, Byron, Leaf River,
Mount Morris, Davis Junction, Adeline, Lee, Rochelle, Forreston,
DeKalb, Shabbona, Hinckley, Creston, Waterman, and Maple Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
